      "date": "2013-04-05 05:33:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nI'm not a big fan of such changes. \n\nIf we moved to always test with multiple MDTs (which I would like to do) then mds-survey would always be skipped. Better to just run it against MDT0000 until it can run against multiple MDTs. \n\nSimilarly for the error messages - if they are too verbose during testing, will they not also be too verbose for normal usage?  Better to fix them, or leave them visible, instead of hiding them for testing and leaving it to cause problems for real users.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
